docs.abstract: Voice-activated helpers can automate life’s little chores, once you get the hang of them.
docs.snippet: Voice-activated helpers can automate life’s little chores, once you get the hang of them.
docs.lead_paragraph: Apple added its Siri assistant to the iPhone 4S model in 2011, giving users a hand-free way to schedule appointments, play music, look up information and perform other basic tasks. Less than a decade later, digital assistants are in a plethora of digital devices, including computers, smart speakers, dashboards and watches, and they can help you ease into the day and keep the household running smoothly.

headline.main: Put Alexa and Siri to Work
headline.print_headline: Getting the Most From Your Digital Helper

docs.abstract: Leaders are divided over a global solution to taxing Silicon Valley giants, a fight for big tax dollars that threatens to disrupt global trade.
docs.snippet: Leaders are divided over a global solution to taxing Silicon Valley giants, a fight for big tax dollars that threatens to disrupt global trade.
docs.lead_paragraph: PARIS — The Trump administration and leaders of other wealthy nations remain at odds over how to tax technology companies and other businesses that operate online, negotiators confirmed on Friday, an impasse that threatens to inflame global trade tensions if not resolved by year’s end.

headline.main: In Talks on Taxing Tech Companies, It’s America vs. the World

docs.abstract: The Amazon founder’s investigation did not find evidence to back his suggestion of a link between Saudi Arabia and the tabloid that gleefully exposed his affair.
docs.snippet: The Amazon founder’s investigation did not find evidence to back his suggestion of a link between Saudi Arabia and the tabloid that gleefully exposed his affair.
docs.lead_paragraph: Almost a year ago, Jeff Bezos hinted that Saudi Arabia had played a role in The National Enquirer’s 11-page exposé of his affair with the Los Angeles television personality Lauren Sanchez. In making the case in a post on the website Medium, Mr. Bezos noted that his newspaper, The Washington Post, had published the Saudi dissident Jamal Khashoggi and had also covered the kingdom’s suspected role in his murder.

headline.main: Jeff Bezos’ Hack Inquiry Falls Short of Implicating National Enquirer
headline.print_headline: Hot Love! Tabloids Embrace New Bezos

docs.lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI — Months after imposing a sweeping communications blackout in Kashmir, the Indian government on Saturday unblocked several hundred websites in the disputed Himalayan region, bringing a tentative end to the world’s longest internet shutdown in a democracy.
